TextBlock.TextLine: Turnhout Willem Sanen
In Antwerpen 12 £s 1681
Mons. in antwoort vanden ul vangisteren sal heden de tijken in de halle
nae sien oftese mij bevallen ende deselve dan op ick stellen t sortement
van ul stalen ben eensdeels voorsien ende inde naeste weeke verwaght noch
meerder pertijen, soo dat ul sal konnen aen 5od guld gerieven
Brussel Andries Ahesens
In Antwerpen 14 feb 1681
Mons. De ul van 11 & 12 deber sijn mij tsamen eerst behandight soo dat ick
de staelen anders niet hebbe connen senden, soo dan ingesloten 2 van de lights
grijs dewelke bij mij hebbe in prijs van 51 t hab van 8 p den staelboeck
us van een soorte van 55 st p hab doch de selve en sijn noch niet
gearriveert soo dat ul daer haestegh mede sijnde daer van niet soude kommen
bedienen als alleen van detwee soo de selve light genoch waren den ssal
boeck gelieft mij wederom te besorgen, laken de ul trato van ƒ300 heb
al dat vol daen volgens ul dat adviseerde, ende salt goetvinden uyt de weird
van o1500 tot last van fran van bruyssende welk ontfangen sijnde ul
sal remitteeren & volgens ordre ul rek seynden terwijlen nae groet
Brussel Ah
Bonnecroy
In Antwerpen 14 feb
Jff. Ick heb den ul van 13 deser wel ontfange ende gesien dat ul de
peninge ul bewesen had becomen, soo dat wij dat dato effen sijn ick
ben gecontramandeert geene cante meer te koope tot haede ordre
over sulx gelieft niet haestigh te sijn als alleenlijk te besorgen den nietr
pattarons & manchett advenant met het truill werck daer van hebbe
gesprocken de welcke verwaghte sal als geseyt waer mede nae groet
London will. pindar
In Antwerpen 15 feb 1681
S in answer to yd of 22 pass do send here inclosed yd acctt. as well of sale as
curitt where by you will finde mee £19:14 t in disbourse - due to you
£42:9:4 besides 17 resting serges the standinghs out debts I can recoves presently
in case I would take bedtijkes in payement, so if you have aminde to
have yd return in that com. Ill procure itt pr. first it could also serve for
atrjall, because bedtijkes are much demanded in England: the actt sent
you ult. june last will shew what is transferred to mr. southell fo that
leave so you, both to do as you thinck most convencent ill willangly
follow yd order whilst I remaine
In Antwarp 18 fe 16:1
London Abram vivian
S my last to you was on the 11 curitt sence non from you, in closed invoyce
of 2 packetts of laces sent to newport to mr. vallego N. 10 will come with these
letters & is extreanly currous & wel assorted N11 will come with next
packett then there is the last packett N. 12 which doth containe 2 broad laces
wherefore beeng ¼ of ayd long will come by the first binlander & thenghan
no more laces with mee acept a fewnew pattarnes, that are att
worck, if you see the se goods you will doubtless beimcorridged so
wish them safe to yd handes. I could wish the goods att hull where here
for our demand com on & have no bayes & our customes beeng much
dimmighed, shall make our gaine more my next shall carry allour acctt
of sale & calculation how thaddrade renders & so remaine
Antwarp 15 ftb
London Henry Maynard
th
S. my last to you was on the 11: curit to which beferma referse you because
sence non from you inclosed a remise on Pietes de cohre junios att 2 uso for
£60 att 35:5: for yd acctt for which please to procure the needfull & note accordingly
our demand for goods comes on so please to dispatch the in ordered goods
the inclosed cullours is also good forlow prijses spanish cloathes sb take some
of them I hope to remitt mote p ferst & att the latter end of this month
send the acctt of sule & so remaine
